        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 5:46AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 545 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from 9 miles southeast of Waynesville to 10 miles
southeast of Hiawassee. Movement was east at 40 mph. An isolated
thunderstorm could develop along this line.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Toxaway, Franklin, Mills River, Graveyard Fields, Tuckasegee,
Horse Shoe, Cruso, Penrose, Wolf Mountain, and B.R. Parkway-Mount
Pisgah To The Nc Arboretum.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 AM EDT for western North
Carolina.</instruction>
